</div>To be fair, Star Trek and Star Wars are more &quot;marketable sci-fi&quot; than &quot;serious sci-fi&quot;.  They're designed to appeal to a larger range of audiences that don't really care about physics.  In the case of Star Trek, it's a soap opera set in space, focusing on the characters as much as (or more than) the situation, especially starting with TNG.<br />
<br />
This doesn't make these two series any less valid than other sci-fi, though, as both are entertaining.</div>
